scopecontent.p:
Appointment of Edward Steptoe to West Point;
                     report of the enforcing bill in the President's
                     proclamation, and the Tariff Bill.

To his brother, on a buying trip to New York;
                     political prospects now look bright, but "the
                     state is lost" to the Anti-Van Buren forces.

The recent death of her husband, Dr. Coleman;
                     the serious illness of Mrs. Henry Peronneau
                     Brown.
